Package: Rdataflow
Type: Package
Title: Visualize Column-Level Data Flow of SQL Scripts
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Jasper", "Cain",
      email = "jcainsecondemail@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Parses a SQL script (T-SQL / SQL Server first) and, using the
    column metadata of the referenced tables, builds a column-level data
    lineage model: which columns each query selects, how tables are joined
    (and on which keys), and what transformations are applied at each stage
    (aggregations, date-diffs, counts, window functions, ...). The lineage
    is rendered as a flow diagram in the style of column-level lineage tools.
